24/02/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Emilia Maslarova, labour minister in the previous cabinet, has been charged with abuse of power, authorities announced on Tuesday (February 23rd).
She is accused of misappropriating 5.5m euros in state funds.
This is the first in a series of indictments that Sofia's chief district prosecutor, Nikolay Kokinov, has promised in the coming days.
(Reuters, Darik, Dnevnik, Sega - 23/02/10)
